**Steps to Reproduce**:

```csharp
using System;
using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;

public class C {
    int? a = null;
    public int M() {
        Release.Assert(a != null);
        return a.Value;
    }
}

internal static class Release
{
	public static void Assert([DoesNotReturnIf(false)] bool condition)
	{
		if (!condition)
			Environment.FailFast();
	}
}
```

**Expected Behavior**:
No warning

**Actual Behavior**:
CS8629: Nullable value type may be null

```cs
class C
{
    void M(object? o1)
    {
        foreach ((var o2, object o3) in new[] { (o1, o1) })
        { 
            o3.ToString();
        }
    }
}
```

The call to `o3.ToString()` should warn, and there should be a warning on converting a nullable reference type to a non-nullable reference type in the assignment to o3.

