**Steps to Reproduce**:

**Test case 1**

```C#
using System;
using System.IO;

class C
{
    static void G()
    {
        using var m = new MemoryStream();
        Console.WriteLine(1);
    }
}
```

The compiler currently emits the following IL and sequence points:

```
.method public hidebysig static 
        void Main2 () cil managed 
    {
        .locals init (
            [0] class C
        )

        IL_0000: nop
        IL_0001: newobj instance void C::.ctor()
        IL_0006: stloc.0
        .try
        {
            IL_0007: ldc.i4.1
            IL_0008: call void [mscorlib]System.Console::WriteLine(int32)
            IL_000d: nop

            // sequence point `}`   [1]
            IL_000e: leave.s IL_001b
        } // end .try
        finally
        {
            // sequence point: hidden
            IL_0010: ldloc.0
            IL_0011: brfalse.s IL_001a

            IL_0013: ldloc.0
            IL_0014: callvirt instance void [mscorlib]System.IDisposable::Dispose()
            IL_0019: nop

            // sequence point: hidden
            IL_001a: endfinally
        }

        // sequence point `}`     [1]
        IL_001b: ret
    }
```

Notice the duplicate sequence points on closing brace [1]. It results in the following ambiguity when someone drags IP to the closing brace:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/41759/61671476-adaa3700-ac9c-11e9-81cd-8f8202f9abea.png)

When stepping we want the debugger to stop on `}` before `Dispose` is called.
The first sequence point on `leave.s` is therefore necessary. The second sequence point on the `ret` instruction should be changed to a hidden sequence point to avoid the ambiguity.

**Test case 2**

In the following case the sequence point for closing `}` of the if statement is not emitted on the `leave` instruction, but on the `nop` instruction following the disposal.
By the time the `}` sequence point (or breakpoint) is hit the object is already disposed, which is unexpected.

```C#
using System;
using System.IO;
class C
{
    public static bool G() => true;

    static void Main()
    {
        if (G()) 
        {
            using var m = new MemoryStream();
            Console.WriteLine(1);
        }
        Console.WriteLine(2);
    }
}
```

```
