```cs
if (o is string text &&
    int.TryParse(text, out var n) &&
    n < 5 && n > -5)
{
}
else
{
}
```

Is refactored to:

```cs
switch (o)
{
    case string text when int.TryParse(text, out var n) &&
    n < 5:
        break;
    default:
        break;
}
```

Not ideal that it trims off `&& n > -5`

I expected:

```cs
switch (o)
{
    case string text when int.TryParse(text, out var n) &&
                        n < 5 && n > -5:
        break;
    default:
        break;
