**Steps to Reproduce**:

Compile the following code:
```cs
#nullable enable
class C
{
    void M(string? s1, string? s2)
    {
        var t = (s1, s2);
        // this works: t.Item1 becomes non-nullable within the switch section
        switch (t)
        {
            case ("", ""):
                t.Item1.ToString(); // no warnings
                break;
        }

        // this doesn't
        switch (s1, s2) // switch ((s1, s2)) doesn't work either
