How would one annotate these scenarios? Is this a supported scenario? From the [LDM notes](https://github.com/dotnet/csharplang/blob/master/meetings/2019/LDM-2019-05-15.md#simple-postconditions) it seems like `[MaybeNull]` is intended to handle unconstrained generics, but that attribute cannot be used here as far as I can tell.

It is currently possible to add/remove the `async` modifier from a local function definition. This may lead to crash when such change is applied while the current active statement is within the method.

Repro:
Place breakpoints as indicated, F5, remove `async` modifier from `f` or add one to `g`. The second edit crashes VS if the IP is subsequently moved to `{` above `Console.WriteLine(2)`.

```C#
using System;

class Program
{
        static void Main(string[] args)
        {
            async void f()
            {
                 Console.WriteLine(1);     // breakpoint
            }

            void g()
            {
                 Console.WriteLine(2);    // breakpoint
            }

            f();
            g();
        }
}
```

We need to disallow adding/removing `async` modifier like we do for regular methods.

